Cost Modeling Investigation

02/06/2015

This is an R Markdown exploratory analysis of Cost Modeling

A model is created based on the mean and median values of each service type for each demographic. The mean is melded with the median to decrease the outlier effects while still allowing them to drive some of the input.

The model is implemented for each individual, each service used is assigned its model cost for that individual. Any known costs are used instead of the model when available. In this way we get the influence of the individual usage rates.
